liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Gary: Do the protesters seem to have a spokesperson? Are they making any demands? There doesn't seem to be any singular spokesperson for the protesters as they're spread across the entire country. Nahel's mother has been a key figure in a lot of the marches so far. One of the family's neighbours told Reuters: "We demand that the judiciary does its job, otherwise we'll do it our way."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: What do the rioters want?

children.content: Do the protesters seem to have a spokesperson? Are they making any demands?
There doesn't seem to be any singular spokesperson for the protesters as they're spread across the entire country.
Nahel's mother has been a key figure in a lot of the marches so far.
One of the family's neighbours told Reuters: "We demand that the judiciary does its job, otherwise we'll do it our way."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A French official, speaking anonymously in line with the presidency’s customary practices, cited an example of the name and address of the police officer who shot at Nahel being published on social media. A prison officer also has seen his professional card going online, the official said, suggesting it could put the person’s life and family at risk. Emmanuel Macron did not specify what type of content he viewed as “sensitive,” but he said he expected “a spirit of responsibility” from the social media platforms.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Why is social media being blamed for fuelling riots?
